cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.IT 

This paper is primarily focused on the networking aspect of 5G architecture, specifically Device to Device (D2D) communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). However, the proposed solution involves the use of intelligent agents, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the decision-making process for transmission mode, which involves optimization and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely category. Additionally, the paper addresses security concerns related to D2D communication, which could fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper also discusses the impact of D2D communication on overall system capacity, which could fall under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
